maml:description.maml:para: Creates a SQLite database connection and transaction object that can be used for batch operations. The caller is responsible for committing or rolling back the transaction. The connection will be automatically created if the database file doesn't exist.
The SQLite connection string for database access.
The file path to the SQLite database. Will be converted to a connection string.
Transaction isolation level. Defaults to ReadCommitted.
Whether to create the database file if it doesn't exist. Defaults to true.
Force a consent prompt even if a preference is already set for SQLite package installation, overriding any saved consent preferences.
Automatically consent to third-party software installation and set a persistent preference flag for SQLite package, bypassing interactive consent prompts.

Creates a SQL Server database connection and transaction object that can be used for batch operations. The caller is responsible for committing or rolling back the transaction. Requires an existing SQL Server database and connection.
The SQL Server connection string for database access.
The name of the SQL Server database. Used with Server parameter to create connection string.
The SQL Server instance name. Defaults to 'localhost'.
Transaction isolation level. Defaults to ReadCommitted.
Force a consent prompt even if a preference is already set for SQL Server package installation, overriding any saved consent preferences.
Automatically consent to third-party software installation and set a persistent preference flag for SQL Server package, bypassing interactive consent prompts.

Creates a new SQL Server database with the specified name on the specified server. Requires appropriate permissions to create databases on the target SQL Server instance. If the database already exists, the operation will be skipped.
The name of the SQL Server database to create. Must be a valid SQL Server database name.
The SQL Server instance name where the database should be created. Defaults to 'localhost'.
Alternative connection string to use instead of Server parameter. Should connect to master database or have appropriate permissions.
Force a consent prompt even if a preference is already set for SQL Server package installation, overriding any saved consent preferences.
Automatically consent to third-party software installation and set a persistent preference flag for SQL Server package, bypassing interactive consent prompts.
